  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Best_Practices__Do_the_Math&quot; name=&quot;XE_Best_Practices__Do_the_Math&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;table bordercolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;23%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
                    Introduction&#xD;
                &lt;/h3>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    Doing a thorough analysis of the business, including crunching some numbers, provides a better picture&#xD;
                    of the business and solution options and will often clearly define the best one. The best approach, at&#xD;
                    first blush, may not prove to be cost-effective once the numbers are crunched.&amp;#160;&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;4%&quot;>&#xD;
                &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;73%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;table style=&quot;HEIGHT: 338px; WIDTH: 672px&quot; bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;5&quot; width=&quot;672&quot; border=&quot;3&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td width=&quot;16%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Benefits&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td width=&quot;84%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Clearer view of possible options and their implications&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Optimized business value&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Reduced scope&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        System can always handle volumes, never at capacity understood and addressed&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Adequate staffing levels to handle demand volume&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Pattern&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Clarify and validate of solutions and options based upon thorough analysis&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Results are based upon mathematical analysis of the solutions and options&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Activities and processes have associated metrics identified and defined including&#xD;
                                        peak loads and staffing levels&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Understand the demand for services in scope services to the architecture effort.,&#xD;
                                        current and projected.&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Use these volumes to assess the cost effectiveness of automation decision. (e.g.,&#xD;
                                        if you only receive 5 requests per year then why automate this type of request)&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Document volumetrics and keep these current (build it and they will come)&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Ensure staffing can handle demand volume and peak load within service level&#xD;
                                        agreements&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Anti-Patterns&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        A lot of system functionality to maintain with no realized value&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        &quot;Lets automate everything&quot; approach&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        The system cannot handle volumes&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;/table>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
